				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Symbols are just "nicknames" for numbers. These numbers can represent memory locations (which is the case of labels and variables) or numeric constants (values you commonly use throughout the program).
<br />
<br />They exist only in the source code to make programming easier (just imagine if you had to remember the addresses of everything!), they do not exist in the assembled program.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

